-- ECB May Take Over Regulation of Europe Banks, Handelsblatt Says
-- B y   A n n e t t e   W e i s b a c h
-- 2012-06-14T19:04:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/ecb-may-take-over-regulation-of-europe-banks-handelsblatt-says.html
The  European Central Bank  might take
over the regulation of European banks,  Handelsblatt  reported,
citing unidentified EU diplomats.  France, the ECB and German Chancellor Angela Merkel back
the plan, which would increase the role of the ECB and would
make the existence of the European Banking Authority
superfluous, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Annette Weisbach in Frankfurt at 
 aweisbach1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
